Each round of the FRI protocol exploits this exact halving. Starting with $|D_0| = 2^n$, after $r$ rounds the domain has size $2^(n-r)$. After $n$ rounds the domain collapses to a single point, at which point the verifier can check the final claim directly. This logarithmic domain reduction is the source of FRI's efficiency.

